blog.name: autonomy1
blog.title: Peter Percival-AUTONOMY
blog.description: Shades, nuances, scraps of existence......looking directly at an object can sometimes be a meaningless, even a destructive use of time…in society we are trained to look at things quickly, process that information and move on to another view…so much information and meaning can be lost in the action of moving on….by changing the expected angle of view, or re-arranging elements of an image one can derive another meaning from it, and if not an absolute meaning an abstract one which makes us look once again…that is all one can ask for, another look…(©) Pete Percival - 2013 All Rights Reserved. blog.description:
My hot takes are simply opinions,

but take it as you like

summary:
All artists are equal 
We may not all have the same skills or style but we are all the same
We use or imagination far more than...
body:
All artists are equal

We may not all have the same skills or style but we are all the same

We use or imagination far more than most so that we can create amazing works of art whether it be music, movies or simple paintings. We all strive to become more advance in our fields and to be appreciated by the outside world for our work

People will complain and tell you that being an artist isn’t a form of work but it is! You can look around and see for yourself. Everyday we watch movies and actors who help paint a story. We hear the soft tunes of our favorite musicians as they weave their loud colors into our lives. Painters and animators create colorful portraits of the world they see and only with a small little brush or pen

No matter what sort of artist you are, you are as equal as the rest of us

An actor is like a painter as a musician is to a director

What we do is amazing and we as a whole must embrace it and each other a little more everyday
